<section class="content-band">
  <div class="container prose">
    <h2>The idea</h2>
    <p>After visiting Florida from England as a child in 2002, the paper maps came home as souvenirs. Years later, they still carry the feeling of first seeing those parks: the colours, the icons, the routes, and the promise that every path led somewhere exciting.</p>
    <p>This site is designed to preserve that feeling while making it easy to browse maps by park, year, decade, and story.</p>

    <h2 id="faq">FAQ</h2>
    <h3>Can I submit a map?</h3>
    <p>Submission details can be added here once the archive workflow is ready.</p>
    <h3>Are the placeholder images final?</h3>
    <p>No. They are temporary visual stand-ins so the site can be designed and tested before the real archive images are uploaded.</p>
